Sentencas: In order to develop a cathode that can be used in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (ITSOFC), the composite materials La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-Ce0.7Bi0.3O2 (LSM-CBO) has been prepared and its electrode performances are investigated below 700degreesC by AC impedance spectroscopy and dc polarization measurements.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of LSM-CBO composite cathode

Sentencas: Results indicate that the oxygen adsorption process is the reaction rate limiting step.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of LSM-CBO composite cathode

Sentencas: The polarization resistance decreases with the increasing of CBO contents.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of LSM-CBO composite cathode

Sentencas: The optimum value of 50 wt.% CBO in LSM results in 1.78 Omega cm(2) area specific resistivity (ASR), which indicates that the LSM-CBO composite electrode is a promising cathode material in ITSOFC.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of LSM-CBO composite cathode
